    <profileDesc>
      <creation/>
      <abstract>
        <p>The Golden Gospel of Dabra Libānos za-Ham is a title (type="académique"&gt;) assigned to an
          archive found in the monastery of Dabra Libānos in the village known as Ham, today's
          Eritrea. This archive was introduced to the academic world in 1901 through the edition by
          the Italian scholar Carlo Conti Rossini under the title L’evangelo d’oro. Carlo Conti
          Rossini had the opportunity to visit the place and see this archive, which resulted in
          publication of the archival documents. 'L'Evangelo d'oro', a title of Conti Rossini's
          publication is used here to difine the totality of Dabra Libānos za-Ham's documents as
          published by the scholar. </p>
      </abstract>
